# encoding: utf-8
=begin

  NameHighlights - Name highlight automation for GemStone IV

  What it does:
    NameHighlights scans live WHO profession and race data, remembers character
    data between runs, and writes a front-end import file that color-codes
    player names.

  Highlight modes:
    profession       Profession controls text and background colors.
    race             Race controls text and background colors.
    race_profession  Race controls text color; profession controls background.

  Manual labels:
    Friend, Family, Enemy, Self, and custom labels can be assigned to names.
    Manual labels override automatic race/profession colors until removed.

  Import model:
    The script writes an import file instead of editing front-end settings
    directly. Import Name highlights to apply player-name colors. Import Custom
    highlights only if you want optional legend labels to color themselves.
    The copy command can merge highlights into Wrayth character XML files, but
    only after paths and duplicate handling are confirmed.

  Front-end support:
    Wrayth/StormFront  Import the generated XML through Settings -> Import.
    Warlock            Import the same XML through Settings -> General ->
                       "Import settings from Wrayth settings file". Select
                       Global to share highlights across characters, or select
                       one character to update only that character.
    Mac compatibility  Supported thanks to Eternil's testing and contribution.
    Wizard/Avalon      Not supported. These older front ends use numeric color
                       palettes instead of the full hex colors used here.

  Basic commands:
      ;namehighlights
          Scans WHO data for the current mode and writes the import file.

      ;namehighlights setup
          Opens the GTK color, mode, tag, and copy setup window.

      ;namehighlights copy setup
          Verifies copy paths before merging highlights into character XMLs.

      ;namehighlights frontend warlock
          Saves Warlock-specific import instructions while still writing Wrayth
          XML, which Warlock can import.

      ;namehighlights help
          Shows the full command list.

       author: Mystienne
  contributor: Peggyanne, Eternil
         game: gs
      version: 1.0.0
         tags: highlights, names, professions, races, colors, tags, customization, frontend
     required: Lich >= 5.11.0
        email: Mystienne@mystienne.com
      discord: Mystienne

=end

